0.720 0.720 0.760 rg 58.00 330.60 3.00 35.50 re f
BT /F2 9.50 Tf 0.040 0.340 0.780 rg 1 0 0 1 72.00 319.60 Tm (SAY \(read this aloud\)) Tj ET
BT /F1 11.00 Tf 0.120 0.120 0.140 rg 1 0 0 1 72.00 303.60 Tm (Let me show you pain point number one, up close. In the old Spring, the framework could not find) Tj ET
BT /F1 11.00 Tf 0.120 0.120 0.140 rg 1 0 0 1 72.00 288.40 Tm (your objects by itself - you had to describe every single one in an XML file. Look at the screen -) Tj ET
BT /F1 11.00 Tf 0.120 0.120 0.140 rg 1 0 0 1 72.00 273.20 Tm (this is what it looked like. Each object is declared by hand, and you manually wire one to another) Tj ET
BT /F1 11.00 Tf 0.120 0.120 0.140 rg 1 0 0 1 72.00 258.00 Tm (with these ref tags.) Tj ET
BT /F1 11.00 Tf 0.120 0.120 0.140 rg 1 0 0 1 72.00 237.80 Tm (Now imagine three problems with this. First, every new class you write means another chunk of) Tj ET
BT /F1 11.00 Tf 0.120 0.120 0.140 rg 1 0 0 1 72.00 222.60 Tm (XML to maintain. Second - and this one really hurt - if you made a typo in a class name here, the) Tj ET
BT /F1 11.00 Tf 0.120 0.120 0.140 rg 1 0 0 1 72.00 207.40 Tm (compiler would not catch it. Your code looked fine, it compiled fine, and then it crashed when you) Tj ET
BT /F1 11.00 Tf 0.120 0.120 0.140 rg 1 0 0 1 72.00 192.20 Tm (ran it. The error was hidden until the worst moment. And third, on real projects, this XML grew into) Tj ET
BT /F1 11.00 Tf 0.120 0.120 0.140 rg 1 0 0 1 72.00 177.00 Tm (hundreds, sometimes thousands of lines. People joked that they spent more time writing XML than) Tj ET
BT /F1 11.00 Tf 0.120 0.120 0.140 rg 1 0 0 1 72.00 161.80 Tm (actual Java.) Tj ET
BT /F1 11.00 Tf 0.120 0.120 0.140 rg 1 0 0 1 72.00 141.60 Tm (So you can see why developers were tired. Spring Boot's answer is to throw nearly all of this away) Tj ET
BT /F1 11.00 Tf 0.120 0.120 0.140 rg 1 0 0 1 72.00 126.40 Tm (and replace it with a couple of simple annotations that the framework discovers automatically. We) Tj ET
BT /F1 11.00 Tf 0.120 0.120 0.140 rg 1 0 0 1 72.00 111.20 Tm (will see exactly how, very soon.) Tj ET
