BT /F1 11.00 Tf 0.120 0.120 0.140 rg 1 0 0 1 72.00 571.90 Tm (Everything Spring Boot does fits neatly into four big gifts. If you understand these four, you) Tj ET
BT /F1 11.00 Tf 0.120 0.120 0.140 rg 1 0 0 1 72.00 556.70 Tm (understand Spring Boot itself. Let me introduce each one - we will go deeper on all of them in the) Tj ET
BT /F1 11.00 Tf 0.120 0.120 0.140 rg 1 0 0 1 72.00 541.50 Tm (next few slides.) Tj ET
BT /F1 11.00 Tf 0.120 0.120 0.140 rg 1 0 0 1 72.00 521.30 Tm (Gift one - auto-configuration. Boot looks at what is in your project and configures sensible defaults) Tj ET
BT /F1 11.00 Tf 0.120 0.120 0.140 rg 1 0 0 1 72.00 506.10 Tm (automatically. This is what replaced all that XML. Gift two - an embedded server. The Tomcat web) Tj ET
BT /F1 11.00 Tf 0.120 0.120 0.140 rg 1 0 0 1 72.00 490.90 Tm (server is now built right inside your app, so there is nothing external to install. You run your app) Tj ET
BT /F1 11.00 Tf 0.120 0.120 0.140 rg 1 0 0 1 72.00 475.70 Tm (like an ordinary Java program. Gift three - starter dependencies. Instead of hunting down a dozen) Tj ET
BT /F1 11.00 Tf 0.120 0.120 0.140 rg 1 0 0 1 72.00 460.50 Tm (libraries, you add one 'starter' and it brings in everything that belongs together, with versions) Tj ET
BT /F1 11.00 Tf 0.120 0.120 0.140 rg 1 0 0 1 72.00 445.30 Tm (guaranteed to fit. And gift four - production-ready features. Things like health checks and metrics,) Tj ET
BT /F1 11.00 Tf 0.120 0.120 0.140 rg 1 0 0 1 72.00 430.10 Tm (built in, so your app is ready for the real world.) Tj ET
BT /F1 11.00 Tf 0.120 0.120 0.140 rg 1 0 0 1 72.00 409.90 Tm (So, four gifts: auto-config, embedded server, starters, and production features. Together, they turn) Tj ET
BT /F1 11.00 Tf 0.120 0.120 0.140 rg 1 0 0 1 72.00 394.70 Tm (that whole painful day of setup into simply 'run the main method'.) Tj ET
0.040 0.520 1.000 rg 58.00 379.50 3.00 214.40 re f
BT /F2 15.00 Tf 0.100 0.100 0.120 rg 1 0 0 1 58.00 360.50 Tm (Slide 8 - Convention over configuration) Tj ET
0.040 0.520 1.000 rg 58.00 343.50 496.00 1.40 re f
BT /F2 9.50 Tf 0.420 0.420 0.460 rg 1 0 0 1 72.00 327.50 Tm (ON SCREEN) Tj ET
BT /F1 10.00 Tf 0.120 0.120 0.140 rg 1 0 0 1 72.00 311.50 Tm (Bullet examples of Boot making intelligent guesses from the classpath, and a key box on day-to-day impact.) Tj ET
0.720 0.720 0.760 rg 58.00 298.00 3.00 35.50 re f
BT /F2 9.50 Tf 0.040 0.340 0.780 rg 1 0 0 1 72.00 287.00 Tm (SAY \(read this aloud\)) Tj ET
BT /F1 11.00 Tf 0.120 0.120 0.140 rg 1 0 0 1 72.00 271.00 Tm (Let's spend a moment on the philosophy that makes all of this possible - convention over) Tj ET
BT /F1 11.00 Tf 0.120 0.120 0.140 rg 1 0 0 1 72.00 255.80 Tm (configuration. It sounds academic, but the idea is simple and clever.) Tj ET
BT /F1 11.00 Tf 0.120 0.120 0.140 rg 1 0 0 1 72.00 235.60 Tm (Instead of forcing you to spell out every little detail, Spring Boot assumes the most common,) Tj ET
BT /F1 11.00 Tf 0.120 0.120 0.140 rg 1 0 0 1 72.00 220.40 Tm (sensible setup - that is the convention - and it only asks you to specify something when your) Tj ET
BT /F1 11.00 Tf 0.120 0.120 0.140 rg 1 0 0 1 72.00 205.20 Tm (needs are different - that is the configuration. In other words, it makes smart guesses.) Tj ET
BT /F1 11.00 Tf 0.120 0.120 0.140 rg 1 0 0 1 72.00 185.00 Tm (Here are some real guesses it makes. It sees you have the web library, so it assumes you are) Tj ET
BT /F1 11.00 Tf 0.120 0.120 0.140 rg 1 0 0 1 72.00 169.80 Tm (building a web app and starts Tomcat on port 8080 - no questions asked. It sees a database) Tj ET
BT /F1 11.00 Tf 0.120 0.120 0.140 rg 1 0 0 1 72.00 154.60 Tm (driver, so it assumes you want a database and sets up the connection. It finds a class marked as a) Tj ET
BT /F1 11.00 Tf 0.120 0.120 0.140 rg 1 0 0 1 72.00 139.40 Tm (controller, so it automatically wires it up to handle web requests.) Tj ET
BT /F1 11.00 Tf 0.120 0.120 0.140 rg 1 0 0 1 72.00 119.20 Tm (So what does this mean for you day to day? It means you write configuration only when you want) Tj ET
BT /F1 11.00 Tf 0.120 0.120 0.140 rg 1 0 0 1 72.00 104.00 Tm (something unusual. If the defaults suit you - and most of the time they do - you write nothing at all.) Tj ET
BT /F1 11.00 Tf 0.120 0.120 0.140 rg 1 0 0 1 72.00 88.80 Tm (Think of it like ordering at a restaurant where the chef already knows the perfect default meal; you) Tj ET
BT /F1 11.00 Tf 0.120 0.120 0.140 rg 1 0 0 1 72.00 73.60 Tm (only speak up if you want to change something.) Tj ET
