BT /F1 11.00 Tf 0.120 0.120 0.140 rg 1 0 0 1 72.00 300.60 Tm (Let's talk about the embedded server, because this was a genuine game-changer. In the old days,) Tj ET
BT /F1 11.00 Tf 0.120 0.120 0.140 rg 1 0 0 1 72.00 285.40 Tm (your app and the web server were separate. You built your app into a file, then you installed a) Tj ET
BT /F1 11.00 Tf 0.120 0.120 0.140 rg 1 0 0 1 72.00 270.20 Tm (Tomcat server on the machine, configured it, and dropped your app inside it. Multiple slow steps,) Tj ET
BT /F1 11.00 Tf 0.120 0.120 0.140 rg 1 0 0 1 72.00 255.00 Tm (and lots of room for mistakes.) Tj ET
BT /F1 11.00 Tf 0.120 0.120 0.140 rg 1 0 0 1 72.00 234.80 Tm (Spring Boot flips this completely. The web server now lives inside your application. So running) Tj ET
BT /F1 11.00 Tf 0.120 0.120 0.140 rg 1 0 0 1 72.00 219.60 Tm (your main method starts both your app and its own web server, in one go. Everything packages) Tj ET
BT /F1 11.00 Tf 0.120 0.120 0.140 rg 1 0 0 1 72.00 204.40 Tm (into a single file - we call it a 'fat JAR' because it contains everything: your code, all the libraries,) Tj ET
BT /F1 11.00 Tf 0.120 0.120 0.140 rg 1 0 0 1 72.00 189.20 Tm (and the server itself. To deploy it anywhere, you just copy that one file to any machine that has) Tj ET
BT /F1 11.00 Tf 0.120 0.120 0.140 rg 1 0 0 1 72.00 174.00 Tm (Java, and type 'java dash jar' and the file name. Done.) Tj ET
BT /F1 11.00 Tf 0.120 0.120 0.140 rg 1 0 0 1 72.00 153.80 Tm (Look at the before-and-after on screen - four manual steps on the left collapse into 'build one file,) Tj ET
BT /F1 11.00 Tf 0.120 0.120 0.140 rg 1 0 0 1 72.00 138.60 Tm (run it' on the right. Think of it like the difference between buying furniture you have to assemble) Tj ET
BT /F1 11.00 Tf 0.120 0.120 0.140 rg 1 0 0 1 72.00 123.40 Tm (versus furniture that arrives ready to use. Boot apps arrive ready to run.) Tj ET
