BT /F1 11.00 Tf 0.120 0.120 0.140 rg 1 0 0 1 72.00 656.50 Tm (Let's pull everything together. Take a breath and look at how much you have learned in one) Tj ET
BT /F1 11.00 Tf 0.120 0.120 0.140 rg 1 0 0 1 72.00 641.30 Tm (session - this is a lot.) Tj ET
BT /F1 11.00 Tf 0.120 0.120 0.140 rg 1 0 0 1 72.00 621.10 Tm (Spring Boot is a layer on top of Spring that removes setup pain through four gifts:) Tj ET
BT /F1 11.00 Tf 0.120 0.120 0.140 rg 1 0 0 1 72.00 605.90 Tm (auto-configuration, an embedded server, starter dependencies, and production-ready features. Its) Tj ET
BT /F1 11.00 Tf 0.120 0.120 0.140 rg 1 0 0 1 72.00 590.70 Tm (guiding philosophy is convention over configuration - sensible defaults you only override when) Tj ET
BT /F1 11.00 Tf 0.120 0.120 0.140 rg 1 0 0 1 72.00 575.50 Tm (needed. A request flows through the front desk, the DispatcherServlet, then to a controller, a) Tj ET
BT /F1 11.00 Tf 0.120 0.120 0.140 rg 1 0 0 1 72.00 560.30 Tm (service, a repository, and the database - each with one job, which we call separation of concerns.) Tj ET
BT /F1 11.00 Tf 0.120 0.120 0.140 rg 1 0 0 1 72.00 545.10 Tm (The at-SpringBootApplication annotation bundles three others, and its run method boots the whole) Tj ET
BT /F1 11.00 Tf 0.120 0.120 0.140 rg 1 0 0 1 72.00 529.90 Tm (app. Dependency injection means the framework creates and wires your objects, giving you) Tj ET
BT /F1 11.00 Tf 0.120 0.120 0.140 rg 1 0 0 1 72.00 514.70 Tm (flexible, testable code. And REST models things as web addresses acted on by verbs.) Tj ET
BT /F1 11.00 Tf 0.120 0.120 0.140 rg 1 0 0 1 72.00 494.50 Tm (If those ideas feel familiar now, you are exactly where you should be. And anything still fuzzy will) Tj ET
BT /F1 11.00 Tf 0.120 0.120 0.140 rg 1 0 0 1 72.00 479.30 Tm (become solid the moment you type it in the lab.) Tj ET
